  "text": "While IE1 stained brightly in the nucleus of the MRC-5 cells transduced with Ad6-IE1, there was little staining seen in the Ad6-mIE1 transduced cells (Fig. 3C, D) . This result was consistent with the immunoblot analysis (Fig. 1A) showing that mIE1 had a lower expression level than IE1 in transiently transfected cell cultures. In addition, the Sp100 staining was visibly different between the cells expressing IE1 and those expressing mIE1. The Sp100 staining in cells expressing IE1 was diffuse in the nucleus, confirming the ability of IE1 to disperse the ND10 structure. [CITATION_1] Such Sp100 staining patterns were not detected in cells expressing mIE1, indicating that the removal of NLS in IE1 was able to reduce its interaction with ND10 (Fig. 3C, D) .",
